id: pm-c90s
title: "pm health 2.3-3.1s in dev repo (~2x the 1.3s baseline): drift-scan cache hit still reads + content-hashes every history stream"
description: "Measured 2026-06-13 (warm, 3 runs): 2326/3076/2590ms vs 1.3s baseline from 2026-05-27 (PR#77). Sandbox health is 180ms, so this is corpus scaling: .agents/pm/history has 1222 streams / 22MB. CPU profile of pm health: ~200ms TOON decode (parseDelimitedValues 87ms + unescapeString 41ms + findClosingQuote 32ms + parseStringLiteral 24ms), hash update 96ms, buildIntegrityCheck self 93ms, 373ms async-IO idle. Root cause: src/core/history/drift-scan.ts (lines 113-115, 171-187) deliberately re-reads the FULL stream and recomputes a content hash even on a metadata cache hit (guard against metadata-stable replacement), so health is O(total history bytes) per run forever; the cache only skips chain replay, not read+hash. Options: trust mtime+ctime+size stat tuple without content re-hash; hash size+first/last 64KB; or make the full-content guard opt-in (pm health --deep). Relates: open auto-compact items reduce corpus size but do not fix the scaling shape."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: audit-2026-06-13,health,history,performance
created_at: "2026-06-12T22:47:21.538Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-19T22:58:06.574Z"
author: audit-quality-agent
parent: pm-y7sc
resolution: "Implemented a split drift-cache verification policy: strict content-hash verification remains the default for validate/history-repair, while pm health uses metadata-only cache hits for warm agent-loop scans."
expected_result: Warm pm health avoids rereading every cached history stream while validation and repair still detect metadata-stable content replacement.
actual_result: "Focused tests, linked tests, full coverage, static quality, security, contracts, changelog check, temp smoke, package dogfood, and Sentry/telemetry gate passed; real-repo warm health measured 615/483/422 ms."
