  "2026-06-17T22:04:54.799Z",codex-audit-20260618,"Sub-agent performance audit evidence: current repo has 1293 history streams, 20691 entries, 24641681 bytes; hotspot remains src/core/history/drift-scan.ts full stream read/content_hash on metadata cache hits. Recommended safe shape: add cacheHitVerification mode, use stat-fingerprint for health warm-cache, keep history-repair --all on content-hash, bump drift cache version, and test health/validate/repair callers separately. Not bundled into GH-262/templates branch because it changes shared drift-scan correctness semantics."
  "2026-06-17T23:12:21.038Z",codex-audit-agent,"Audit decision: performance subagent confirmed pm health hotspot remains drift-scan cache-hit content hashing across 1293 streams/24.6MB; this branch did not change it because a cache-hit verification mode/stat-fingerprint optimization needs separate correctness design. Current command-profile fixture paths remain low-ms; package-first dogfood slowest health brief/health around ~516ms in isolated temp project."
  "2026-06-19T22:58:00.092Z",codex-sdk-cli-20260620,"Evidence: implemented cacheHitVerification option in src/core/history/drift-scan.ts, kept strict default for validate/history-repair, opted pm health into metadata cache hits, bumped drift cache version to 3, and exposed health details.cache_hit_verification=metadata. Verification: focused drift/health/validate/repair tests passed; pm test --run passed 3/3 linked tests; pnpm build passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 100/100/100/100 (4697 tests); pnpm quality:static passed; pnpm audit found no vulnerabilities; pnpm security:scan found no secrets; pnpm contracts:check passed; pnpm changelog:pm:check passed before close; temp dir smoke init/create/health/validate passed; npm run dogfood:package-first passed 87 commands; Sentry/telemetry gate passed with 0 critical/high and telemetry error rate 1.81%. Dependency note: commander@15 not upgraded because it requires Node >=22.12.0 while package.json supports >=20; @types/node@26 left unchanged to avoid raising compile surface beyond supported Node line."
